<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="193" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1155,1434]" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,210,1229,1253]" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,203,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">Note</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[218,401,1229,1253]" class="Anthozoa" family="Alcyoniidae" genus="Alcyonium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bursa">
<emphasis box="[218,401,1229,1253]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">Alcyonium bursa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the basionym for a sponge (M. Spencer-Jones, pers. comm.). The sole known extant original material, an illustration in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, J." box="[430,550,1265,1289]" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" refId="ref5047" refString="Ellis, J. (1755) An Essay towards a Natural History of the Corallines and other Marine Productions of the like Kind commonly found on the Coasts of Great Britain and Ireland to which is added the Description of a large Marine Polype taken near the North Pole, by the Whale-fishers, in the Summer of 1753. A. Millar, London, xxviii + 103 pp., XXXIX pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10146" type="book" year="1755">Ellis (1755</bibRefCitation>
: t.17,f. B,C &amp; D.), represents a form of polyp-forming animal. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Alcyoniidae" genus="Alcyonium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bursa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">Alcyonium bursa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also, though erroneously, been treated by phycologists as the basionym for the green alga 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Agardh" authorityYear="1822" baseAuthorityName="Olivi" box="[1236,1389,1301,1325]" class="Bryopsidophyceae" family="Codiaceae" genus="Codium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="bursa">
<emphasis box="[1236,1389,1301,1325]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">Codium bursa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the correct authorship for the latter name is 
<taxonomicName authority="(Olivi) C. Agardh" authorityName="C. Agardh" authorityYear="1822" baseAuthorityName="Olivi" box="[578,861,1337,1361]" class="Bryopsidophyceae" family="Codiaceae" genus="Codium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="bursa">
<emphasis box="[578,671,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">C. bursa</emphasis>
(Olivi) C.Agardh
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brodie, J. &amp; Maggs, C. A. &amp; John, D. M." box="[874,1133,1337,1361]" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" refId="ref4944" refString="Brodie, J., Maggs, C. A. &amp; John, D. M. (2007) Green seaweeds of Britain and Ireland. British Phycological Society, London, 250 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Brodie 
<emphasis box="[955,1002,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">et al</emphasis>
., 2007: 190
</bibRefCitation>
).”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1155,1434]" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">
This statement contains several clear errors and we believe it is scientifically and nomenclaturally incorrect. The purpose of this article is to demonstrate that Linnaeus’ 
<taxonomicName box="[736,918,1409,1433]" class="Anthozoa" family="Alcyoniidae" genus="Alcyonium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bursa">
<emphasis box="[736,918,1409,1433]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">Alcyonium bursa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not the basionym of any sponge known to us.
</paragraph>
